<h2><b>The quiz shall primarily consist of two stages:</b></h2>


<br>	
<ul>

<li> <b>The top six teams will make it onto stage. The quiz from here on will be subdivided into five rounds :</b></li>
<li><b>	Sports: 1 question per team, 10 points per question, 5 for passed questions, no negative marking.</b></li>
<li><b>	Technical: 1 question per team, 10 points per question, 5 for passed questions, no negative marking.</b></li>
<li><b>	Current Affairs: 1 question per team, 10 points per question, 5 for passed questions, no negative marking.</b></li>
<li><b>	Buzzer Round: 1 question per team, 20 points per question, no passing, -5 for incorrect answers.</b></li>
<li><b>	Link the images: Four images will be shown to each team; they will be required to find the common link between them. 1 question per team, 5 points for identifying each image, 20 points for finding the correct link, no negative marking.</b></li> 
<li><b>	Rapid fire round: Each team gets a minute to answer a maximum of 10 questions and awarded 5 points each. Speed is critical. 
</b></li>

</ul>
